Getting Washington to back down would mean yielding to the demands, but submitting publicly to the United States would be too embarrassing for Chinese President Xi Jinping.
Still, experts say that if Beijing plays its cards well, pressures from the U.S. trade war could positively help China in the long run by reducing interdependence between the two economies.
